summary: i'm gonna be honest with you. i dont know why people are freaking out over taylors posts. i'm hating the editing in those pics....
question: i'm gonna be honest with you. i dont know why people are freaking out over taylors posts. i'm hating the editing in those pics. it looks like a 5 year old is dealing her social media. she's beautiful but those colors and bubbles ugh
answer: To be honest, I love them. I’m not freaking out over them because I promised after the 1989 era taking a negative toll on my emotional health that I would take a step back and wouldn’t get to that point again, but I think they’re really pretty and like the filters. Do I see it getting oversaturatedvery quickly if she reuses filters constantly? Sure. But for now it looks really nice in my opinion.

body: Ok this is gonna sound really dumb and weird but like cos I’m always thinking about Taylor and sometimes meeting her, I can’t help thinking that if I ever went to a secret session how lonely I would be until I saw Taylor? Like obviously when Taylor would come in the room I would be with my best friend, but in all the videos and story’s I see and hear, everyone always talks about how they finally got to meet there ibfs there and they made so many good friends and they saw people they knew etc. But like for me?? I literally don’t know anyone personally on here or any other social platform other than my irl swiftie friends, and I just don’t do well in new social situations or making friends. And I swear I’m not just saying that to be a rElAtAbLe teen, I struggle with it every day to the point where it stops me from going out, ruins the whole day and my mood or I end up stressing over something that I did or said for the next few days. summary: I just love your attitude toward Taylor's music. One of Taylor's hallmarks is that she continues to evolve as an artist. It...
question: I just love your attitude toward Taylor's music. One of Taylor's hallmarks is that she continues to evolve as an artist. It seems to me that every new album uses what she's learned from previous albums, but she's never going to do any album's 2.0 version. I think her next album will progress logically from Rep, even if it's "happy." (And I think it will be more finding light than glittery, teen-age happy.) Thoughts?
answer:
I too love that she changes with every album. To be clear, I don’t necessarily think that’s the right path for every artist, and I don’t think every artist is capable of it, but I love that Taylor does it. I feel like it’s such an honest way of being an artist, it’s like, “here’s how I’m feeling right now, and how I want it to sound, and I’m sorry if that doesn’t match with what you expected, but this is how it is… in this very moment.” And there’s certain boldness to it, and I love seeing boldness in people.

I have no idea where next album is gonna take us, and I suck at predictions or, to be honest, caring much about making them. When the time’s right, we’re gonna see/hear her next project and then we’ll know.
